# .specify/config.example
# Example configuration for local template selection
#
# Copy this file to .specify/config and customize for your project:
#   cp .specify/config.example .specify/config

# =============================================================================
# TEMPLATE ARGUMENTS (Required)
# =============================================================================
# Specify which template to use by providing space-separated arguments.
# These arguments must match the template filename pattern:
#   spec-kit-template-{arg1}-{arg2}-v{version}.zip
#
# Format: "{arg1} {arg2}"
#
# Examples:
#   TEMPLATE_ARGS="claude sh"    # Matches: spec-kit-template-claude-sh-v*.zip
#   TEMPLATE_ARGS="claude py"    # Matches: spec-kit-template-claude-py-v*.zip
#   TEMPLATE_ARGS="test js"      # Matches: spec-kit-template-test-js-v*.zip
#
TEMPLATE_ARGS="claude sh"

# =============================================================================
# TEMPLATE VERSION (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# By default, the system automatically selects the latest version when multiple
# templates with the same arguments exist. You can override this to pin to a
# specific version.
#
# Format: "MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH" or "vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH"
#
# Examples:
#   TEMPLATE_VERSION="0.0.78"    # Pin to specific version
#   TEMPLATE_VERSION="v0.0.78"   # Also valid with 'v' prefix
#
# Leave commented to always use the latest version (recommended):
# TEMPLATE_VERSION=""

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - Template files must be placed in the directory where you run the
#   create-new-feature.sh command
# - If this config file is missing or TEMPLATE_ARGS is not set, the system
#   will prompt you interactively to select from available templates
# - Template filenames must follow the exact pattern:
#   spec-kit-template-{arg1}-{arg2}-v{version}.zip
